## Description
Create a GitHubService class similar to BeadsService to manage GitHub integration state.

## Instructions
1. Create `src/service/github-service.ts` with `GitHubService` class
2. Service should:
   - Store GitHub enabled state
   - Provide `isGitHubEnabled()` method
   - Provide `createDefinition()` for template registration
3. Follow same pattern as `src/service/beads-service.ts` but simpler (no context injection needed)

## Implementation
```typescript
export interface GitHubServiceOptions {
  coderConfig: CoderConfig;
  logger: Logger;
}

export interface GitHubDefinition {
  enabled(): boolean;
}

export class GitHubService {
  private readonly githubEnabled: boolean;

  constructor(options: GitHubServiceOptions) {
    const detector = new GitHubDetector({ logger: options.logger });
    this.githubEnabled = detector.isGitHubEnabled(options.coderConfig);
  }

  isGitHubEnabled(): boolean {
    return this.githubEnabled;
  }

  createDefinition(): GitHubDefinition {
    return { enabled: () => this.githubEnabled };
  }
}
```

## Files to Create/Modify
- Create: `src/service/github-service.ts`
- Modify: `src/service/index.ts` (add export)

## Dependencies
- Depends on GitHubDetector (oc-ki19)

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] GitHubService class created
- [ ] isGitHubEnabled() works
- [ ] createDefinition() works
- [ ] Exported from service module

## Description
Add timing instrumentation to GitHubDetector methods - these use execSync and are likely slow.

## Instructions
1. Add timing to each detection method:
   - detectGitDirectory() 
   - detectGitHubRemote() - calls `git remote -v`
   - isGhCliInstalled() - calls `command -v gh`
   - isGitHubEnabled() - orchestrates the above

2. Pattern:
   ```typescript
   detectGitHubRemote(): boolean {
     const start = Date.now();
     try {
       // ... existing logic ...
       return hasGitHubRemote;
     } finally {
       this.logger.debug("detectGitHubRemote completed", { durationMs: Date.now() - start });
     }
   }
   ```

3. For isGitHubEnabled(), log total time including all sub-calls

## Files to Modify
- src/github/detector.ts

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] All 4 methods have timing logged
- [ ] Debug level logging
- [ ] Can identify which execSync call is slowest
- [ ] Tests still pass

